1
00:00:01,230 --> 00:00:05,160
Episode 18

2
00:00:14,410 --> 00:00:17,670
Kim Ian

3
00:00:57,470 --> 00:00:58,870
What are you doing?

4
00:00:58,870 --> 00:01:01,480
Why are you scribbling on the sheet of music?

5
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:06,560
There. Look.

6
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:13,760
If you put your hand exactly here iike this, haven't you joined your hand to mine?

7
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:18,630
What is this?  So childish.

8
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:21,100
- Childish?
- Totally childish.

9
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:23,590
Where did you learn to do this?

10
00:01:23,590 --> 00:01:25,720
From my hyung.

11
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:28,360
- Hyung?
- Yeah.

12
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:31,800
I must tell him immediately. That you called it childish.

13
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,400
You must be nuts.

14
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:39,060
- Give it back. I have to call him.
- I won't.  You can't.

15
00:02:13,220 --> 00:02:17,190
The customer you have called is not available.

16
00:02:17,190 --> 00:02:19,350
You can leave a message after the beep.

17
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:24,090
I haven't heard from you since yesterday. Did something happen at the orchestra?

18
00:03:13,370 --> 00:03:15,170
Why did you come?  I'm getting discharged soon.

19
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:17,150
We  just came from work.

20
00:03:17,150 --> 00:03:21,120
It's the only useful tradition our orchestra has and we can't stay.

21
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:23,310
But the level of participation drops every year.

22
00:03:23,310 --> 00:03:26,160
There's barely any members gathered here.

23
00:03:27,010 --> 00:03:29,870
Now that we have visited the hospital, shall we go?

24
00:03:29,870 --> 00:03:33,300
We're leaving already?    We had a hard time coming ...

25
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:35,130
A patient needs to rest.

26
00:03:35,130 --> 00:03:37,640
Don't get out. We're all busy.

27
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,660
It's narrow and small.

28
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:42,350
Excuse me, Je Ni. Je Ni.

29
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:44,520
Yes?

30
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:48,810
Did something happen to Hong Yi Yeong?  I can't contact her.

31
00:03:48,810 --> 00:03:51,870
Yi Yeong took a leave yesterday.

32
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:54,380
Didn't she contact you all day?

33
00:03:54,380 --> 00:03:58,660
Didn't she turn in her resignation?  There a rumor going around that she quit.

34
00:03:58,660 --> 00:04:01,070
A resignation?  She quit?

35
00:04:01,070 --> 00:04:03,840
No, no.  Never.

36
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,570
Why are you talking nonsense.  She didn't resign.

37
00:04:06,570 --> 00:04:08,540
Everyone said so.

38
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:11,380
But why are you asking?

39
00:04:11,380 --> 00:04:13,770
Come out.  Hurry.  Bye.

40
00:04:13,770 --> 00:04:16,110
Bye.

41
00:04:27,370 --> 00:04:30,330
Mr. Tone-Deaf

42
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:38,550
Police Station

43
00:04:44,550 --> 00:04:48,160
Hyung, please go to Hong Yi Yeong's house and check if she is there.

44
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,900
If she's not there, bring my car.  Do it quickly.

45
00:04:57,950 --> 00:04:59,860
It's that day.  Some time in August.

46
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:04,700
After receiving a report from the neighborhood head, our sergeant was on the move and I followed him.

47
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:09,290
So, you're saying that was the day Hong Yi Yeong was discovered.

48
00:05:09,290 --> 00:05:10,060
Yes.

49
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:11,890
Looking at your face, I see I am correct.

50
00:05:11,890 --> 00:05:16,300
But ... do you have something to say about the accident?

51
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:18,970
Although I don't know if you remember,

52
00:05:18,970 --> 00:05:24,000
the night before there was a hit-and-run accident.

53
00:05:25,540 --> 00:05:26,640
Right. Right.

54
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:31,620
Your possessions were found in the car of the person who died that day in the hit-and-run accident.

55
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:33,510
I got a call to go and collect them.

56
00:05:33,510 --> 00:05:37,740
The name of the person who died that day was Kim Ian.

57
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,990
That day I ...

58
00:05:42,890 --> 00:05:46,680
I stabbed him that day.

59
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,180
What?

60
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:53,500
Yes.  She is here right now.

61
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:57,440
I verified her identity.   She is Hong Yi Yeong herself.

62
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:03,710
Yes. Just as I promised, I called you privately.

63
00:06:03,710 --> 00:06:06,580
You can go home now.

64
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:11,580
What?  I  told you that I stabbed Kim Ian that day.

65
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:14,410
You seem a smart person, what's wrong with you?

66
00:06:14,410 --> 00:06:18,700
I told you earlier, right?  The case was closed as an accident a year ago.

67
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:22,400
The hit-and-run culprit turned himself in and has already served his sentence.

68
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,340
Do you have any proof that you stabbed him?

69
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:26,010
When I was at the hospital to receive counseling,

70
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:29,560
I said with my own mouth that I stabbed him.

71
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:33,870
I really did stab that person.

72
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:37,610
I don't have it now, but I even had the knife.  My bag was also found  in his car.

73
00:06:37,610 --> 00:06:40,980
And, now, please ...

74
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:44,390
can't you look into the accident again?

75
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:49,340
Do you have a grudge against me?

76
00:06:52,130 --> 00:06:54,090
I beg of you.  Please reinvestigate the case.

77
00:06:54,090 --> 00:06:59,400
Somehow, I want to atone for what I did to Kim Ian and finish everything.

78
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,880
Are you saying she turned herself in?

79
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:07,010
Unbelievable.

80
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:08,850
All right.

81
00:07:08,850 --> 00:07:12,690
Did you really send her home?  Check it out all the way to the end.

82
00:07:12,690 --> 00:07:17,350
Damn, what are we going to do with Yun Yeong Gil?

83
00:07:17,350 --> 00:07:20,640
I going to go crazy because of that bastard.

84
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:26,090
Do you understand what I said?

85
00:07:26,090 --> 00:07:29,380
We cannot reinvestigate a closed case, so just go home safely.

86
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:33,020
Don't ever come back here, please.

87
00:08:12,020 --> 00:08:14,700
I will bring flowers.

88
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,970
I'm sorry.

89
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:25,350
I am powerless and stupid. There's nothing I can do.

90
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,460
Rest in peace. Kim Ian. 1991/02/28 - 2018/8/19

91
00:08:29,460 --> 00:08:33,260
I'm sorry that I couldn't answer your phone call that day.

92
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:37,420
I'm sorry I am alive without you.

93
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:55,410
Yes, Je Ni. It's Jang Yun.

94
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:58,840
Could Hong Yi Yeong be anywhere other than home or the art center?

95
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:01,160
She's not answering her phone.

96
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:06,200
Is that so?  Yes.

97
00:09:24,990 --> 00:09:27,090
And this.

98
00:09:27,090 --> 00:09:30,470
Sorry for being late. I see you have already packed.

99
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:33,290
I'm just getting discharged.  There nothing urgent for you to come here.

100
00:09:33,290 --> 00:09:35,830
You should have just skipped coming if you're busy.

101
00:09:36,930 --> 00:09:40,100
He's happy to see you.  He's just pretending he's not.

102
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:42,100
Let's hurry out of here. I called a taxi.

103
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:46,800
Dad,  you can't eat just anything.  Avoid foods which are too greasy.

104
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:50,990
All right. Today I'll restrain nyself. I'll start eating tomorrow.

105
00:09:50,990 --> 00:09:54,110
By the way, I spoke to your conductor.

106
00:09:54,110 --> 00:09:56,210
He's coming to the house tomorrow.

107
00:09:56,210 --> 00:09:58,940
Did you call him?

108
00:09:58,940 --> 00:10:01,340
I did it because I didn't think you would.

109
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:04,150
He was so very very grateful that I called.

110
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:09,370
My mom's amazing.  She's already talking to the conductor.

111
00:10:09,370 --> 00:10:12,610
I'm not a player whom he could resist.

112
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:10,210
I'm surprised. What are you doing?  Are you following me?

113
00:12:10,210 --> 00:12:14,470
You met my father. Did you contact him?  Or have you known each other from the beginning?

114
00:12:14,470 --> 00:12:19,090
I'm not saying.   If you're curious, ask him directly.

115
00:12:19,090 --> 00:12:20,950
You two are father and son.

116
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:24,490
Although you seem to hate each other to death.

117
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:31,370
Did you see Hong Yi Yeong yesterday? Did you take her somewhere?

118
00:12:31,370 --> 00:12:36,510
Hong Yi Yeong? Has she disappeared somewhere?

119
00:12:38,310 --> 00:12:43,510
Don't say.  Did you come  looking for me to see if I kidnapped her?

120
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:49,000
Don't laugh. Tell  me whether or not you saw her yesterday.

121
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:52,590
How would I know where she is?

122
00:12:52,590 --> 00:12:56,100
She just ran away from you.

123
00:12:57,390 --> 00:12:59,960
If you have a brain, try to think about it.

124
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:04,120
How could she continue to date the hyung of the person she stabbed?

125
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:08,660
Unless she's out of her mind. Don't you agree?

126
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:10,810
Don't laugh.

127
00:13:58,510 --> 00:14:01,890
Is it all right to be going around like this in your condition?

128
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:09,810
Explain this to me.

129
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:24,260
Why do you keep following that bastard? I told you to lay low for a while.

130
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:28,350
I looked for him because I wanted to find out whether he had met Hong Yi Yeong.

131
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:35,110
What haven't you told me? What's his connection to my father?

132
00:14:35,110 --> 00:14:37,830
Don't say that bastard is my father's minion.

133
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:44,920
I'm sorry but I can't answer that question. My livelihood would be on the line.

134
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:49,940
Go home. You almost got killed, so please stay quiet.

135
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:17,300
♫ Because I can't forget, I cry. ♫

136
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:21,630
It's irrelevant, but recently I started working out.

137
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:24,230
From my house to your house by bicycle it's 40 minutes.

138
00:15:24,230 --> 00:15:26,100
♫ While I'm looking for you who won't come  ♫

139
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:30,530
Because your house is on top of a hill, it's a ten-minute jog from the entrance to your neighborhood.

140
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:32,740
I was thinking about going there.

141
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:37,340
It's been a long time since I had a break.  If I call you from in front of your house, will you swear at me?

142
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:39,530
If I text, will you look out of the window for just one minute?

143
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:44,200
By the way, your aunt invited me over. Did you hear?

144
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:47,170
♫ Tell me what should doin’ it now  ♫

145
00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:48,920
♫ Even if it's a lie, tell me ♫

146
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:52,330
♫ Saying everything can be taken back ♫

147
00:15:52,330 --> 00:15:55,940
♫ Even it is a brief moment ♫

148
00:15:55,940 --> 00:15:59,520
♫ When I call you thousands of times ♫

149
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:02,990
♫ I found myself but I’m still losing myself ♫

150
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:06,360
♫ Can you come back to me? ♫

151
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:11,380
♫ Because I can't forget.  I cry. ♫

152
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:18,940
♫ Even if it is a lie.  I try ♫

153
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:32,750
When did you meet my father?  Why did you meet him?

154
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:36,720
You aren't surprised that I know he's your father?

155
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:40,850
It was expensive but boring intel.

156
00:16:40,850 --> 00:16:43,000
Why would you pay for something like that?

157
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,000
I needed it.

158
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,190
Did you know he's going onto the orchestra's board?

159
00:16:49,870 --> 00:16:51,950
I see you didn't know.

160
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:55,900
Using my own wits, I told him I would have you cut from the orchestra.

161
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:58,330
He rejected the idea.

162
00:16:58,330 --> 00:17:02,390
He said he would leave you there temporarily. He had lost interest.

163
00:17:02,390 --> 00:17:04,730
Why are you doing this to me?

164
00:17:04,730 --> 00:17:08,400
What do you want to know? Don't beat around the bush and say it directly.

165
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:11,200
Why did you go to the extent of changing your name and approach Hong Yi Yeong?

166
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:14,770
Why are you curious? Whether I'm interested in her or not is my own business.

167
00:17:14,770 --> 00:17:16,270
There are two reasons.

168
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:22,130
A year ago, I saw something on the day Kim Ian died.

169
00:17:23,390 --> 00:17:25,550
Were you there with him?

170
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,990
What did you see that day?

171
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:32,740
If you answer me, I'll tell you.

172
00:17:32,740 --> 00:17:37,530
What's your reason for doing this?  Do you need money, what is it?

173
00:17:38,420 --> 00:17:41,020
First answer my question.

174
00:17:41,020 --> 00:17:45,850
Kim Ian did not die in an accident that day. Right?

175
00:17:45,850 --> 00:17:48,920
Who killed Kim Ian?

176
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,090
Who killed him?

177
00:17:52,790 --> 00:17:54,730
Hong Yi Yeong?

178
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:27,420
Keep calm.  It's okay.

179
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:32,400
It's just thunder.

180
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,900
Take a deep breath.

181
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:40,410
Big breath in. Breathe out.

182
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:42,680
Breathe in.

183
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,670
Breathe out.

184
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:51,940
Should I make you laugh in ten seconds?

185
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:53,700
How can you?

186
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:57,100
Wait a second.

187
00:19:00,390 --> 00:19:04,560
♫  There is a man

188
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:08,090
♫  He loves you so much.

189
00:19:08,090 --> 00:19:11,680
♫  There is a man.

190
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:15,720
♫ He couldn't say  I love you

191
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:20,260
♫ If I reach my hand out to you

192
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:23,180
♫ I will touch you.

193
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:34,200
♫ I'm the one who cares for you more than you do yourself.

194
00:19:41,530 --> 00:19:42,710
What was that?

195
00:19:42,710 --> 00:19:45,380
See.  You laughed, didn't you?

196
00:19:45,380 --> 00:19:48,370
You really are an awful singer.

197
00:19:48,370 --> 00:19:51,890
I am.  Hong Yi Yeong ...

198
00:19:51,890 --> 00:19:54,040
Yeah?

199
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:59,660
There is one thing I didn't tell you.

200
00:20:01,010 --> 00:20:02,970
I should tell you now.

201
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:05,080
To me?

202
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:08,340
What is it?

203
00:20:16,630 --> 00:20:18,430
Who are you?

204
00:20:30,310 --> 00:20:32,260
Who is it?

205
00:20:32,260 --> 00:20:34,200
You, who are you?

206
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:37,190
Who is doing this to us?

207
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:45,540
Who is it? Please don't come close.

208
00:20:45,540 --> 00:20:47,180
Yi Yeong!

209
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:50,830
Who are you?  Who are you?

210
00:20:57,130 --> 00:20:59,530
Yi Yeong! Hong Yi Yeong!

211
00:20:59,530 --> 00:21:02,520
Don't come close. Don't come.

212
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:05,720
Don't come close.

213
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:09,510
Don't come close. Don't come.

214
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:11,600
Don't come close.

215
00:21:12,870 --> 00:21:14,380
Don't come.

216
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:16,490
Hong Yi Yeong!

217
00:21:52,620 --> 00:21:54,520
Maestro Nam

218
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:57,010
I ran all the way to your house and I'm exhausted.

219
00:21:57,010 --> 00:22:01,390
Right now I'm in front of your house. I think I'm going to die.

220
00:22:08,350 --> 00:22:10,630
Tell me what you saw that day.

221
00:22:10,630 --> 00:22:14,090
You saw something and you want to know what happened that day?

222
00:22:14,090 --> 00:22:16,930
Does it have any connection to Ian?

223
00:22:18,370 --> 00:22:23,250
That day ... Did you see someone you shouldn't have seen?

224
00:22:23,250 --> 00:22:25,190
Who was it?

225
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:30,010
If I tell you, what are you going to give me?

226
00:22:30,010 --> 00:22:33,040
So what do you want?

227
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:38,310
It's Nam Ju Wan. I want him fired from the orchestra.

228
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:43,690
Is that what you want?

229
00:22:43,690 --> 00:22:48,730
Yes.  I think you can do it.

230
00:22:50,620 --> 00:22:56,510
That night, all the cars going to the after-party at Professor Song's house were full.

231
00:22:56,510 --> 00:23:00,170
Because I thought I couldn't go there that way, I was going by taxi.

232
00:23:00,170 --> 00:23:05,030
Hong Yi Yeong couldn't get into a car either, so she caught a taxi.

233
00:23:05,030 --> 00:23:08,590
Kim Ian pulled in front of her taxi.

234
00:23:08,590 --> 00:23:10,400
And?

235
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:14,300
Hong Yi Yeong got into his car.

236
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:20,400
And another car followed the two of them.

237
00:23:21,310 --> 00:23:23,130
A second car?

238
00:23:24,850 --> 00:23:27,080
Nam Ju Wan's car.

239
00:23:50,780 --> 00:23:53,050
Did you really run all the way here?

240
00:23:53,050 --> 00:23:54,790
I told you I would.

241
00:23:54,790 --> 00:23:57,190
I said I'd come riding my bicycle and in the middle of the way I switched to walking.

242
00:23:57,190 --> 00:24:01,080
But I thought I was going to die. You can't do this in the summer.

243
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:05,700
Of course. Thank's goodness you didn't get wiped out.

244
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:30,100
Has it been two days?  It's good to see you outside.

245
00:24:56,010 --> 00:24:58,680
Mr. Tone Deaf

246
